.TH SPTOP 1 "Spherepop Toolkit"
.SH NAME
sptop \- semantic observability dashboard
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B sptop
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B sptop
provides a live, read-only overview of semantic system properties
relevant to Spherepop and RSVP-style frameworks.

Unlike traditional process monitors, sptop does not permit control,
termination, or modification of processes. It is an observational tool.

.SH SEMANTIC METRICS
The displayed metrics are symbolic diagnostics:

.TP
.B Determinism Index
Heuristic indicator of replay stability.

.TP
.B Refusal Capacity
Whether non-execution paths are structurally present.

.TP
.B Perturbation Stability
Sensitivity to irrelevant variation.

.TP
.B Didactic Pressure
Degree to which systems favor procedural outputs.

.TP
.B Constraint Coupling
Whether constraints remain linked to execution.

.SH INTERACTION
The interface accepts minimal input:

.TP
.B q
Quit sptop.

.TP
.B r
Force immediate refresh.

No other controls are provided.

.SH PHILOSOPHY
sptop embodies the principle that observation should not collapse
into intervention. It makes semantic structure visible without
rendering it executable.

.SH SEE ALSO
spdoctor(1), spscan(1), spreplay(1), sprefuse(1)

